_source.productName: Cancer and Cartwheels - Dr Jo Prendergast at the Brisbane Powerhouse
_source.productDescription:
Join psychiatrist, award-winning comedian, and cancer survivor Dr. Jo Prendergast as she brings her critically acclaimed solo comedy show, Cancer and Cartwheels to the Brisbane Comedy Festival this May. 

Jo is making her way to the Brisbane stage with a hilarious, heartwarming, and deeply meaningful performance about overcoming breast cancer, reclaiming her cartwheeling abilities, and navigating the changes that come with illness, aging, and menopause.

Written during her cancer treatment, Jo blends comedy, storytelling, musical numbers, and video clips to entertain and educate. Experience a journey of resilience, self-discovery, and humour, turning her personal experience into absurd and uplifting moments that will leave you laughing and reflecting.

Jo's battle with cancer left her right arm disabledcould she ever cartwheel again? In this show, she shares the emotional and physical challenges of surviving cancer, while celebrating her triumph over adversity. Cancer and Cartwheels also explores vital themes like early cancer detection, the often-overlooked symptoms of menopause, and the emotional toll of cancer treatments.

But it's not all heavythe show is packed with comedy skits, musical acts, and laugh-out-loud moments, while also addressing serious issues like toxic positivity, body neutrality, and healthcare inequality. Whether you're a cancer survivor, someone navigating the ups and downs of aging, or simply a fan of stand-up comedy with heart, this show will leave you uplifted, informed, and entertained.

Whether you grew up on their records or you've just discovered the magic of the Fab Four, this evening is your chance to experience the music that changed the world  performed live by an incredible lineup of local talent:
Ayla, David Flower, Frank and Louis, MOU, Calan Mai, and The Team Musicare Band.

Sing along to your favourites  from Let It Be and Here Comes the Sun, to Come Together and Hey Jude  and take a trip down Penny Lane with fellow Beatles fans under the stars.

Tickets are only AUD15 plus booking fee  affordable, fun, and fab.

Food and drinks available on-site. All ages welcome.

Join in for an evening celebrating freshwater produce, featuring a live cooking demonstration by renowned chef Matt Golinski. 

The night begins with Bundaberg local Tracy Patterson sharing expert tips on preparing freshwater fish, showcasing her favourite recipes and techniques. 

Guests will enjoy cheese boards before Matt Golinski takes the spotlight for a live cooking demonstration. He will guide attendees through the best techniques to cook freshwater fish, offering insights on flavour pairings and preparation methods.  

Dinner - 7.00pm, guests will enjoy a catered dinner inspired by the evening's lessons.

As dinner is finalised, live acoustic music will set the tone for a relaxed and social evening. 

This evening will leave attendees with valuable culinary knowledge, great food experience, and an enjoyable night of learning and connection.

The Borumba Deer Park will host 'Lake to Plate' in the Stock Yard area of the park.

This is a BYO event, and we encourage the community to support Borumba Deer Park by making a weekend of it. Enjoy the beauty of the Mary Valley, with a day on the water followed by an unforgettable evening.

Proudly Sponsored by Queensland Hydro and the Queensland Government.

The Chillagoe Rodeo is a proud small-town event that delivers an action-packed weekend filled with adrenaline-pumping rodeo action, making it a must-attend event in Far North Queensland. Held every May, this iconic rodeo has been a community favourite since the 1970s, growing in popularity and prestige thanks to the dedication of committees past and present.

Perfect for the whole family, the Chillagoe Rodeo features show-stopping entertainment, including bull riding, barrel racing, and a variety of thrilling rodeo sports that promise to keep spectators on the edge of their seats. The event also proudly supports the local community, with successful charity auctions where 50% of proceeds benefit the Chillagoe Hospital, showcasing the towns spirit of giving back.

Beyond the rodeo arena, the event hosts horse sports competitions, ensuring theres something for every equestrian enthusiast. The Chillagoe Rodeo not only offers top-tier entertainment but also provides the perfect opportunity to explore the historic mining town of Chillagoe, known for its limestone caves, marble bluffs, and outback charm.

Join them this May for an unforgettable weekend of family fun, community spirit, and thrilling rodeo action at the Chillagoe Rodeoa true outback Queensland experience you wont want to miss!

Get ready to be swept off your feet by the delightful Australian Celtic Women show! This all-female ensemble welcomes you on a whimsical journey through rolling hills, enchanting moors, and heavenly melodies that will make your heart sing. Enjoy their angelic voices, dazzling costumes, and electrifying fiddle performances that sprinkle pure magic into the air.

Formed to celebrate Australias unique Celtic heritage and showcase the talent of women in Celtic music, the group come with diverse backgrounds in opera, musical theatre, folk, rock, pop and Celtic genres. Their harmonies, described as out of this world, combine award-winning expertise from various musical and performance disciplines.

With the soulful sounds of Celtic instruments, ACW serves up an unforgettable feast of warmth, nostalgia, and sheer joy that will leave you clamouring for an encore. Each talented artistbringing their expertise from classical to Celtic, rock to popadds a unique spark, weaving a vibrant tapestry of music that lights up the stage and your spirit!

From haunting acapella vocals, rock drum solos, duelling bagpipes and whirlwind fiddle; Australian Celtic Women take you on a journey where your feet tap, your hands clap, you laugh out loud and you cry (sometimes all in the same song)

_source.productName: 12 Gold Bars - A Celebration of Status Quo - Capalaba
_source.productDescription:
This incredible group of musicians is dedicated to recreating the sound and energy of one of the most beloved bands of the 70s and 80s, and they're taking on Status Quo's legendary album 12 Gold Bars.

Featuring some of the most talented musicians and vocalists in the country including ex-Angels and Choirboys member James Morley, Pete Robinson from Russell Morris Band, along with Eddy Santacreu, and David Kirby from Queen Orchestrated, this group brings a level of professionalism and dedication to their craft that sets them apart from other cover bands. They've spent countless hours studying the intricate instrumental arrangements and harmonies that made Status Quo such a hit, and they're ready to deliver an unforgettable performance for fans old and new.

At their upcoming show, you can expect to hear every track from 12 Gold Bars, including hits like "Rockin' All Over The World" "Whatever You Want Down Down and "Caroline." The band's attention to detail is unmatched, from the faithful reproductions of the original songs to the signature guitar riffs that made Status Quo a household name.
